instructions = 'This week\'s contest crossword revolves around four consonants. This week\'s contest answer is the only grid entry that contains all four of those consonants.'
explanation = '<MA>PUB JOKE (1-Down)</MA><TEXT>This puzzle was released during the 2008 Olympic Games in Beijing, and played on the differences between the formerly used Wade-Giles transliteration of China\'s capital (Peking) and the modern Pinyin version (Beijing). This meant changing a "P" sound to a "B" or a "K" sound to a "J," so "field hockey" became FIELD HAJI, "triple jump" became TRIBBLE JUMP, "pole vault" became BOWL VAULT, "water polo" became WATER BOLO, and "basketball" became BASS JET BALL. The four important consonants are thus P, B, K, and J, and the only entry containing all four of them is PUB JOKE at 1-Down.</TEXT>'
